International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 19 Aug 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31449


Anthrax, Kazakhstan
-------------------
Information received on [and dated] 19 Aug 2019 from Dr Tursyn Kabduldanov, deputy chairman, Committee for Veterinary Control and Supervision, Ministry of Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 12 Aug 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 16 Aug 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Olginka, Arshaly, Akmolinskaya [Aqmola]
Date of start of the outbreak: 12 Aug 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 323 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0
Equidae / 53 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 113 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Equidae / 126 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.31 / 0.00 / 0.00 / 0.31
Equidae / 0 / 0 / - / 0
Sheep / 0 / 0 / - / 0
Swine / 0 / 0 / - / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology: source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; quarantine; zoning; disinfection; no treatment of affected animals.
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species (Total vaccinated)
Akmolinskaya [Aqmola] / Cattle (323), Equidae (53), Sheep (113), Swine (126).

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Reference Centre for veterinary (national laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 16 Aug 2019 / Positive
Republican veterinary laboratory (national laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 16 Aug 2019 / Positive

Future reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak location: [go to the OIE website to see their showing of this outbreak in north-central Kazakhstan.]

